@node install "Installation and starting CYCAS for the first time"


   Installation and starting CYCAS for the first time.




   System requirements


   Software:    Kickstart 3.0, 3.1
                Workbench 3.0, 3.1

   Minimum:     68020, 2MB RAM, HD

   Recommended: 68030/68882 or 68040/60,
                6MB RAM and more
                HD and graphics board.




   Double click  the   install   icon   and   follow   the
   instructions.

   Open the Help Drawer and  start the  SetupHelp-Program.
   Now, you can choose your favourite WWW - Browser   for
   online help (e.g. IBrowse, Voyager, AWeb, etc).

   Starting  CYCAS  for  the  first time, the program will
   adopt the screen mode of your workbench. You may change
   the screen mode  you  want  to  work in by pressing the
   right mouse button (pull-down menus)  and  by selecting
   the menu 'GUI-Setup'.

   You may change the screen font also. Avoid  using large
   font  sizes  as  they may not  fit the user  interface.

   This setup can be saved.

   By choosing  the item 'Project/Load', you can  try  the
   example drawings.

   At the right bottom edge of the user interface there is
   a 'Help' button. Here, you  can start  the online help.

   If CYCAS does not show the english localized interface,
   make sure to have selected  'english' as available and
   / or prefered language in Worbench/Prefs/Locale.


@endnode

@node support "About this release"


   This release of CYCAS 1.78 for Amiga is offered to use for free.

   The public licence code is 548200795.

   No support is given.



   Have fun with Cycas.

